# Scraper conventions

## Instances

- `get_scraper(email, cookie)` — cached singleton per email (booking path; no password).
- `refresh_scraper(email, password)` — login + replace cache (login form only).

## Auth

- Session via `cloudscraper`; cookies pickled on `User.cookie`.
- Stale cookie without password → `PasswordRequired`.
- Login failure → `LoginError`; API 302 to login → `InvalidBox`.

## Key methods

| Method | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `book` | Auto-reserve class |
| `cancel_booking` | User-initiated cancel |
| `get_classes` / `get_week_classes` | Schedule UI |
| `wait_until_event` | SSE wait for class availability |
| `get_user_booked_classes` | Sync |
| `get_training_descriptions` | WOD text cache |

## Exceptions

All defined in `exceptions.py`; raised from `scraper.py`. Booker maps each to wait/retry/abort — see [docs/wodbuster-integration.md](../docs/wodbuster-integration.md).

## Safety

- Use `_safe_log_response_content` for logs; never log full cookies/passwords.
- WodBuster HTML/JSON formats are fragile — preserve existing parsing patterns.
